  <h1>Deep Fried Cheese Rolls</h1>
  <p>Crunchy on the outside, super cheesy on the inside. These deep fried cheese rolls are perfect as a snack, party food, or a side dish with dips.</p>

  <h2>Ingredients (makes 10–12 rolls)</h2>

  <h3>Cheese filling</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>300 g mozzarella, cut into sticks</li>
    <li>150 g cheddar cheese, cut into sticks</li>
    <li>2 g black pepper</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Rolls</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>10–12 spring roll wrappers</li>
    <li>30 ml water (for sealing the wrappers)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>For frying</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>800–1000 ml neutral frying oil (enough to deep fry)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Optional dips</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Chili mayo</li>
    <li>Garlic mayo</li>
    <li>Sweet chili sauce</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Instructions</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Cut the mozzarella and cheddar into sticks (about 8–10 cm long).</li>
    <li>Place a spring roll wrapper on a clean surface (like a diamond shape).</li>
    <li>Add 1–2 cheese sticks in the center and sprinkle with a little black pepper.</li>
    <li>Fold the bottom corner up over the cheese, fold in the sides, then roll tightly.</li>
    <li>Seal the final corner with a little water so it sticks properly.</li>
    <li>Repeat until all rolls are ready.</li>
    <li>Heat oil to <strong>170–180°C</strong>.</li>
    <li>Fry the rolls in small batches for <strong>2–3 minutes</strong> until golden and crispy.</li>
    <li>Remove and drain on paper towels for 1 minute.</li>
    <li>Serve immediately while the cheese is still melted.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Tips</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Don’t overfill the wrappers, or the cheese may burst out while frying.</li>
    <li>For extra security: freeze the rolls for 15–20 minutes before frying (helps prevent leaking).</li>
    <li>Keep the oil temperature steady so they don’t become greasy.</li>
    <li>Air fryer option: brush with oil and cook at 200°C for 8–10 minutes (not as crispy as deep frying, but still good).</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Required Equipment</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Knife and cutting board</li>
    <li>Deep pot or fryer</li>
    <li>Thermometer (recommended)</li>
    <li>Slotted spoon or tongs</li>
    <li>Paper towels</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Allergen Information</h2>
  <p>Contains dairy (cheese). Wrappers usually contain gluten. Check ingredients for possible allergens.</p>

